var title_f33_10_33965="Primary VF outcome GISSI";
var content_f33_10_33965=[" <div id=\"graphicsToolbar\">",
"  <div id=\"graphicsCopy\">",
"   &copy;2013 UpToDate",
"   <sup>",
"    &reg;",
"   </sup>",
"  </div>",
"  <div id=\"graphicsLinks\">",
"   <a href=\"?imageKey=CARD%2F69187&amp;source=image_view&amp;view=print&amp;elapsedTimeMs=1\" onclick=\"\">",
"    <img alt=\"Print this page\" src=\"./../images/icn_print.myextg\" title=\"Print this page\"/>",
"   </a>",
"   <a class=\"icontxt textLink\" href=\"?imageKey=CARD%2F69187&amp;source=image_view&amp;view=print&amp;elapsedTimeMs=1\" onclick=\"\" title=\"Print this page\">",
"    Print",
"   </a>",
"   <a class=\"etacLink\" href=\"#\">",
"    <img alt=\"Email graphic(s)\" src=\"./../images/icn_email.myextg\" title=\"Email graphic(s)\"/>",
"   </a>",
"   <a class=\"icontxt textLink etacLink\" href=\"#\" title=\"Email graphic(s)\">",
"    Email",
"   </a>",
"  </div>",
" </div>",
" <div class=\"graphic\">",
"  <div class=\"figure\" style=\"width: 470px\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    Primary VF after acute MI predicts early, but not late, mortality",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 445px; height: 340px; background-image: url(data:image/gif;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    In the GISSI-2 trial of 9720 patients with acute myocardial infarction (MI), the occurrence of early (&le;4 hours) and late (&gt;4 to 48 hours) primary ventricular fibrillation (PVF) predicted a higher in-hospital morality compared to the absence of ventricular fibrillation. However, PVF, regardless of timing, did not affect the six month prognosis. In contrast, the prognosis was much poorer among patients with nonprimary VF which occurred &ge;48 hours after the MI.",
"    <div class=\"footnotes\">",
"    </div>",
"    <div class=\"reference\">",
"     Data from: Volpi A, Cavalli A, Santoro L, et al. on behalf of the GISSI-2 Investigators, Am J Cardiol 1998; 82:265.",
"    </div>",
"   </div>",
"  </div>",
" </div>",
"</div>"].join("\n");
